<doc>
  <member name="MF_TOPONODE_FLUSH_MODE">
    <summary>
      <para>Defines when a transform in a topology is flushed.</para>
    </summary>
    <seealso href="https://docs.microsoft.com//windows/desktop/medfound/mf-toponode-flush-attribute">MF_TOPONODE_FLUSH</seealso>
    <seealso href="https://docs.microsoft.com//windows/desktop/medfound/media-foundation-enumerations">Media Foundation Enumerations</seealso>
  </member>
  <member name="MF_TOPONODE_FLUSH_MODE.MF_TOPONODE_FLUSH_ALWAYS">
    <summary>
      <para>The transform is flushed whenever the stream changes, including seeks and new segments.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="MF_TOPONODE_FLUSH_MODE.MF_TOPONODE_FLUSH_SEEK">
    <summary>
      <para>The transform is flushed when seeking is performed on the stream.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="MF_TOPONODE_FLUSH_MODE.MF_TOPONODE_FLUSH_NEVER">
    <summary>
      <para>The transform is never flushed during streaming. It is flushed only when the object is released.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
</doc>